Just a little question on why using the named view and not the component directly.

I started learning today the named views feature of vue-router and this question stuck into my mind.

Given this app template: 

    &lt;app-header&gt;&lt;/app-header&gt;
    &lt;router-view name=&quot;app-header&quot;&gt;&lt;/router-view&gt;
    &lt;router-view&gt;&lt;/router-view&gt;

On the first two lines above we&#39;re targeting the same component.  
The reason I discovered for using named views in this case is the following: you don&#39;t need to check the current route path and show/hide the `&lt;app-header&gt;` on specific paths, vue-router knows to hide the named view if the path is not the one it was defined on.

Are there any other reasons to use the named view instead of just rendering the component?

Thanks!

